### Add Inline Embed in New Namespace Without Reload (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/packages/embeds/embed-core/index.html

Initializes Cal.com with a specific namespace ('withoutReloadNamespace') and then embeds an inline element. This function is useful for adding embeds without requiring a full page reload, especially when managing different embedding contexts.

```javascript
function addInlineEmbedInNewNamespaceWithoutReload(selector) {
  Cal("init", "withoutReloadNamespace", {
    debug: true,
    calOrigin: window.calOrigin,
  });
  Cal.ns.withoutReloadNamespace("inline", {
    elementOrSelector: selector,
    calLink: "pro?case=addInlineEmbedInANewNamespaceWithoutReload",
    config: {
      "flag.coep": "true"
    }
  });
};
```

